WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.290
 SPC Performance # 72130 EX35 / G37 / 370Z Welcome to the front upper arm installation video. 

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:18.080
 The SPC # 72130 fits the Fairlady Z 34, Skyline V36, Skyline Coupe CKV 36, Skyline Crossover J50. 

00:00:19.090 --> 00:00:24.080
 Follow the safety measures. 

00:00:28.240 --> 00:00:33.230
 Jack up the vehicle and support it with rigid rack. 

00:00:37.180 --> 00:00:42.170
 Remove the front tire. 

00:00:46.150 --> 00:00:52.040
 Remove the bolts and nuts holding the upper link to the knuckle. 

00:01:10.160 --> 00:01:15.250
 Remove the upper link from the knuckle. 

00:01:16.110 --> 00:01:22.170
 Support the knuckle with a band etc. so that the brake line and the ABS wire can not be pulled. 

00:01:28.260 --> 00:01:35.230
 Remove the two bolts holding the genuine upper link to the body. 

00:01:55.050 --> 00:02:02.250
 The upper nut holding the strut may be loosened in order to remove the bolt holding the upper link. 

00:02:10.030 --> 00:02:16.100
 Move the lower link so that the bolt passes through the spring. 

00:02:26.080 --> 00:02:31.250
 Remove the genuine upper link from the vehicle. 

00:02:37.290 --> 00:02:50.050
 To change the camber and caster, mount the offset ball joint in the appropriate direction, referring to the attached installation manual. 

00:02:53.150 --> 00:03:01.030
 Vary the caster and camber angles by offsetting the ball joints in 12 different directions. (SPC patent) 

00:03:04.230 --> 00:03:09.110
 Lightly tighten the nut at the top of the ball joint. 

00:03:15.120 --> 00:03:25.180
 L and R are written so that the upper arm may not be mistaken. 

00:03:29.150 --> 00:03:36.140
 Attach the upper arm to the vehicle using the two mounting bolts. 

00:03:48.090 --> 00:03:53.080
 We do not tighten the bolts here. 

00:03:58.240 --> 00:04:03.250
 Return the ball joint to the knuckle. 

00:04:08.250 --> 00:04:15.030
 Replace and tighten the bolts and nuts. 

00:04:31.210 --> 00:04:38.280
 Jack up at the lower link to load the suspension. 

00:04:44.280 --> 00:04:53.020
 Now tighten the bolt securing the upper arm. 

00:04:54.030 --> 00:04:58.280
 If you loosened the strut mounting nut, tighten it now. 

00:05:01.100 --> 00:05:07.250
 Return the front tire and tighten it with the specified torque. 

00:05:19.200 --> 00:05:30.010
 Loosen the top nut to adjust the camber and slide the ball joint to the desired value. 

00:05:37.160 --> 00:05:44.060
 Tighten the upper nut to the specified torque. 

00:05:45.110 --> 00:05:51.160
 Adjust the toe to check the wheel alignment and do a trial ride. 

